data.description: LOVE THIS HOME AND EMERALD MOUNTAIN SUBDIVISION! ESCAPE the city and Enjoy GOLF, Tennis, Pickle Ball, walking trails, and many other amenities of Emerald Mountain.  The Emerald Mountain Volunteer Fire Department helps keep Homeowner's Insurance Premiums lower.  WELCOME HOME to a Beautifully designed home in cul-de-sac. Love the curb appeal, floor plan, high ceilings and trey ceilings, lots of natural light from the many gorgeous transom windows, four spacious bedrooms with plenty of closet space, a large laundry room, half bath, and so much more. A private hallway leads to the spacious master suite with two walk-in closets, a garden tub, and a separate shower. The fourth bedroom currently serves as an office.  It would also be perfect for a home school room, library, craft room, or den. Don't miss the impressive kitchen back splash and granite countertop installed in 2021. Plenty of spaces for dining: formal dining room, kitchen breakfast bar, breakfast room, and large back patio.  Love the location of this home tucked away in a cul-de-sac on a .62 +/- acre lot in the Redland school district.  Enjoy the large and private back patio and fully fenced backyard. Plenty of parking with an extra parking pad outside the garage.  Come and discover the beauty of Emerald Mountain subdivision and 105 Acorn Way.
